	Posts: 176<br><br>



	Server: Innoruuk<br>





                Guild: <br>



<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=140750&resize=true" target=_blank>Magelo Link</font></a>

<br>	
</td>
	<td bgcolor="#000000" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >No developer ever said taunt was top hate + 1. All they ever said was that it put you at the top of the hate list by a small amount.<br />
<br />
<a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=1390" target="_blank">Here is a question about taunt and Gordon Wrinn's reply from Sony's boards ca. April 26, 2000:</a>  <br />
<br />
<blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >quote:</font><hr><br />
Source: Everquest Gameplay Forum.<br />
<br />
<i>I am posing a question here for all the classes to respond to. Should the cap for taunt be raised for all the taunt capable classes? (War, SK, Pal, Rang). I think it should be raised. With the new more powerful spells, increased skill caps (offense/weapon skill), new weapons with high taunt factors, and the new disciplines, the taunting classes are going to have a hellacious time keeping anything on them.</i><br />
<br />
The skill level associated with taunt interacts with your level to determine how likely the taunt is to be successful.  It does not control the level of success.  A successful taunt will always make the creature shift to you, assuming that it can be taunted (Yes, some creatures are untauntable). <br />
Taunt makes a creature hate you just a little bit more than it hates the next guy on the list.  In other words, multiple successful taunts, or taunting a creature that is already attacking you doesn't do anything extra. <br />
<br />
I hope that clears up how Taunt works. <br />
<br />
- Gordon<br />
<hr></blockquote> <br />
<br />
Hanadan (Solinar) has done a test in CoD demonstrating that taunt generates top hate + some amount between something like 90 and 170 (the value of the two cleric nukes he tested) -- he suggests it's actually 2xlevel, so 130 for 65s. <br />
<br />
Gordon's reply says some mobs can't be taunted; maybe others are taunt resistant. He mentions between an interaction between skill level and player level, but it's hard not to think mob level plays a role too.<br />
<br />
I'm not sure what to make of Brutul's results. I guess we certainly didn't know what we thought we knew about taunt. The recurrent pattern of 4 "successful" taunt messages before getting aggro is a little scary.</font></p>
	
