	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Nice testing...I think other classes need to read this, if nothing else than to realize that this is the only way Warriors can get agro over them, and that it simply doesn't work as well as we thought.  Also to see those streaks of Taunt failures, ouch.  Took 7 taunts (42 seconds minimum) in your first original test to get agro, and 6 (36 seconds minimum) in the second...from a 65 Warrior with, most likely, 230 skill in Taunt.  If Taunt doesn't put you on the top of the agro list on a success, that's an explanation...if it DOES everytime, then Taunt really does suck.</font></p>
	
