	<td bgcolor="#000000" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >During the "back and forth" testing it was very clear that difference in distance to the mob, even a very small difference, significantly effects who the mob hits when both toons are high on the aggro list.  Several times I got into a situation where the cleric would get hit but if he backed up a few steps the mob would go back to hitting the warrior.  If the cleric got close again, he would get hit again.  This was very repeatable and it was clear that distance to the mob was the only factor in whether the cleric got hit or not.  He only had to move a very small amount to flip the mob back and forth.  This is a factor that is very hard to control in these tests and may explain some anomalies.</font></p>
	
